node.text: 𝘽𝙚 𝙩𝙝𝙚 𝙣𝙚𝙭𝙩 𝙖𝙢𝙗𝙖𝙨𝙨𝙖𝙙𝙤𝙧 , 𝙡𝙚𝙩𝙨 𝙘𝙤𝙡𝙡𝙖𝙗. 𝙈𝙚𝙨𝙨𝙖𝙜𝙚 𝙤𝙪𝙧 𝙖𝙘𝙘𝙤𝙪𝙣𝙩 𝙜𝙞𝙧𝙡 🎇 @  @gassiniofficial

RECREATING ASIAN TV CHARACTERS! 📺 .
Thank you to everyone who volunteered your favourite TV characters played by Asians! It was really interesting to explore TV shows I don’t watch and to find out how Asians are represented in TV from different eras, languages, genres, and platforms.
.
This challenge was borne out of a desire to dress up as my favourite TV characters but I soon felt a bit hollow dressing up as characters who didn’t reflect what I looked like. I’m so happy to learn that Asian representation is growing in mainstream media in various genres!
.
A moment of silence for the characters I wanted to dress up as but didn’t have the clothes to do so 😢
.
Swipe to see side by sides of the characters I recreated:
1. Jung Hee-joo, played by @ssinz7 on Memories of the Alhambra
2. Eleanor Young, played by @ramonabishyoung on @neverhaveiever
3. Eve Polastri, played by @iamsandraohinsta on @killingeve
4. Jang Man-wol, played by @dlwlrma on Hotel Del Luna
5. Doctor Kang Mo-yeon, played by @kyo1122 on Descendants of the Sun
Have you seen that TikTok trend where people film themselves in different outfits for a particular show? And that particular track as well!! It’s so good✨
Pls do a Kiki one next from Kiki's delivery service haha
@therealquirkyteal me too, Hyun Bin was so charming there too!!!
I loved Park Shin Hye’s outfits in Memories of the Alhambra!!! 😍
@massielmendozaa HAHAHA THANK YOU!! a lot of old clothes and hand me downs tbh - I’m started to dig into the archives for these challenges!!
I JUST WANNA KNOW HOW BIG YOUR CLOSET ISSSSS WOMAN 😂 ALSO - good work!
